# migrated from tests/cases/gen_read.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test gen_read]
# gen41: induce the generative model from real text. "read: <passage>" now
# ALSO feeds each clause's word stream into the continuation model (the same
# bigram/trigram machinery `learn sequence:` uses), so generation grows from
# the prose parrot0 actually reads -- not only from explicit teaching. The two
# halves built so far (the reasoning KB and the generative loop) now share one
# input path. Held-out content; nothing here is authored into the binary.
> read: the otter swims downstream. the otter swims often.
< Learned 0 fact(s), skipped 2.
# Generation reflects the read text's transitions, frequency-then-order ranked.
> say the
< the otter swims downstream
> say otter
< otter swims downstream
> say swims
< swims downstream
# Fact extraction (gen32) is untouched: the same read path still lifts facts,
# and the very same prose seeds the model -- proving the model IS the corpus.
> read: kira is a pilot. kira flies jets.
< Learned 1 fact(s), skipped 1.
> is kira a pilot?
< Yes.
> say kira
< kira is a pilot

